cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DL 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for language proficiency classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses various machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses both theory-guided and data-driven features, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves cross-lingual classification, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
